.TH "acpi_pm_device_sleep_state" 9 "acpi_pm_device_sleep_state" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
acpi_pm_device_sleep_state \- Get preferred power state of ACPI device.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" acpi_pm_device_sleep_state
.BI "(struct device *dev "  ","
.BI "int *d_min_p "  ","
.BI "int d_max_in "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
Device whose preferred target power state to return.
.IP "d_min_p" 12
Location to store the upper limit of the allowed states range.
.IP "d_max_in" 12
Deepest low-power state to take into consideration.
Return value: Preferred power state of the device on success, -ENODEV
if there's no 'struct acpi_device' for \fIdev\fP, -EINVAL if \fId_max_in\fP is
incorrect, or -ENODATA on ACPI method failure.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
The caller must ensure that \fIdev\fP is valid before using this function.
